other_tests.findings: Endoscopic removal of stone(s) from biliary tract.

The liver appears normal in echotexture with no focal liver lesions identified. The partially visualized pancreas appears unremarkable. Multiple mobile gallstones within the gallbladder. The gallbladder appears mildly distended with a thin wall. The common bile duct shows at least two stones and is dilated measuring up to 10 mm.
